natural problem: Eleven rectangular 9-inch by 12-inch pictures hang on a wall. How many square inches of the wall's surface area are covered by the pictures?
natural solution: We multiply all three numbers together. There are two quick ways of doing this; both are shown below: $$11\cdot 9 \cdot 12 = (10 + 1)\cdot 108 = 1080 + 108 = \boxed{1188}$$$$11\cdot 9 \cdot 12 = 99\cdot 12 = (100 - 1)\cdot 12 = 1200 - 12 = \boxed{1188}$$

a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes inch :: real
assumes h0 : "1 * inch = 1"
shows  "11 * (9 * inch) * (12 * inch) = 1188 * (inch powr 2)"
